{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RZX7TKqEYTqZzxLDs7ifaD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive report.\n\n## Project State Summary: Loops 9-10 Delivery and Daemon Automation Groundwork\n\nBased on my exploration of the codebase, git history, loop specifications, and implementation notes, here's what was delivered in loops 9-10 and the existing automation/daemon groundwork:\n\n### **Loop 9: Docs Change and CI Improvement Flow Execution**\n**Status:** Completed and merged to master\n\n**Delivered:**\n- **Generalized Workflow Engine**: Introduced `FlowSemantics` struct that maps each flow preset's structural roles (planning stage, execution stage, remediation stages, late stages, prompt review stage)\n- **Flow Semantics Derivation**: `stage_plan_for_flow()` and related functions that generate stage sequences for `standard`, `docs_change`, `ci_improvement`, and `quick_dev` presets\n- **Engine Generalization**: Converted `execute_standard_run` → `execute_run` and `resume_standard_run` → `resume_run` with backward-compatible wrappers\n- **Stage-Specific Logic Elimination**: Replaced all hardcoded references to `StageId::Planning`, `StageId::Implementation`, etc., with flow-semantic lookups for:\n  - Remediation restart point (execution stage)\n  - Amendment drain point (planning stage)\n  - Completion-round restart (planning stage)\n  - Prompt-review pause check (flow-specific stage if present)\n  - Late-stage detection (completion-round advancement)\n\n**CLI Updates:**\n- `run start` and `run resume` now accept `DocsChange` and `CiImprovement` projects (removed `UnsupportedFlow` guard for these)\n- `QuickDev` remains unsupported (guard still in place)\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- 3 new Gherkin feature files: `run_start_docs_change.feature`, `run_start_ci_improvement.feature`, `run_resume_non_standard.feature`\n- Dedicated `flow_semantics_test.rs` with structural mapping tests for all four presets\n- Engine-level tests for docs/CI flows with real FS stores, journal, and resume paths\n- All 230+ unit tests and 67+ CLI tests pass\n\n**Files Modified/Created:**\n- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` — `FlowSemantics`, stage planning\n- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` — Generalized orchestration\n- `src/cli/run.rs` — Flow preset dispatch\n- Multiple test files\n\n---\n\n### **Loop 10: Requirements Drafting and Project Seed Handoff**\n**Status:** Completed (currently in loop 10 planning phase per git history)\n\n**Delivered:**\n- **Agent Execution Generalization**: Introduced `InvocationContract` enum that decouples agent execution from workflow-only `StageContract` usage, enabling requirements contracts without adding to project `StageId` enum\n- **Requirements Domain Context**: Full `requirements_drafting` bounded context with:\n  - `RequirementsRun` state model (persisted at `.ralph-burning/requirements/<run-id>/run.json`)\n  - `RequirementsStatus` enum: `drafting`, `awaiting_answers`, `completed`, `failed`\n  - `RequirementsStageId` enum: `QuestionSet`, `RequirementsDraft`, `RequirementsReview`, `ProjectSeed`\n  - Four structured contract types with validation pipelines:\n    - `question_set` — stable question IDs, prompt text, required flags\n    - `requirements_draft` — problem summary, goals, non-goals, constraints, acceptance criteria, recommended flow\n    - `requirements_review` — approval/conditional/rejection/request-changes outcomes with findings\n    - `project_seed` — project ID, name, recommended flow, final prompt.md\n  \n- **CLI Commands**: All four commands implemented and wired:\n  - `requirements draft --idea \"<text>\"` — creates run, generates questions, transitions to `awaiting_answers` or continues if no questions\n  - `requirements quick --idea \"<text>\"` — skips questions, executes draft→review→seed in one command\n  - `requirements answer <run-id>` — opens `answers.toml` in `$EDITOR`, validates, resumes from answer boundary\n  - `requirements show <run-id>` — displays run state, seed path, and suggested `project create` command\n\n- **Durable State Management**:\n  - Persists `run.json`, `journal.ndjson`, `answers.toml`, `answers.json`, `history/payloads/*`, `history/artifacts/*`, `seed/project.json`, `seed/prompt.md`\n  - Seed rollback semantics: if `prompt.md` fails after `project.json`, both are removed and run transitions to failed\n  - Journal-append failure recovery at seven boundaries with `FailingJournalRequirementsStore` test fixtures\n\n- **Integration Points**:\n  - Reuses `agent_execution` pipeline for capability checks, timeout, cancellation, session management\n  - Respects planner/reviewer defaults for backend selection and raw-output persistence\n  - Requires `sessions.json` in run directory (created by `FsRequirementsStore`)\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- 24 new unit tests (model, contracts, renderers, service integration)\n- 10 Gherkin conformance scenarios in `requirements_drafting.feature`\n- 7 fault-injection tests covering journal-append failures at each boundary\n- Total: 272 tests passing (248 existing + 24 new)\n\n**Files Modified/Created:**\n- `src/contexts/agent_execution/` — Generalized contract interface\n- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/` — New bounded context (model, contracts, renderers, service)\n- `src/cli/requirements.rs` — Four CLI commands\n- `src/adapters/fs.rs` — `FsRequirementsStore` implementation\n- `src/adapters/stub_backend.rs` — Requirements-stage canned payloads\n- `tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature`\n- `tests/unit/requirements_drafting_test.rs`\n\n---\n\n### **Daemon and Automation Groundwork Already in Place**\n\n**CLI Stubs:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/daemon.rs`\n- Commands defined but not yet implemented: `daemon start`, `daemon status`, `daemon abort`, `daemon retry`, `daemon reconcile`\n- Returns `NotYetImplemented` error for all commands\n\n**Automation Context:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/mod.rs` exists as a placeholder\n- Contains only `CONTEXT_NAME = \"automation_runtime\"`\n\n**Workspace Directory Structure (Loop 3 - Workspace Governance):**\n- `REQUIRED_WORKSPACE_DIRECTORIES` includes:\n  - `.ralph-burning/projects/` — project records\n  - `.ralph-burning/requirements/` — requirements runs\n  - `.ralph-burning/daemon/tasks/` — task queue\n  - `.ralph-burning/daemon/leases/` — lease coordination\n- Initialized by `initialize_workspace()` in `src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs`\n- Validated in conformance scenarios (`workspace_init.feature`)\n\n**Conformance Expectations (from workspace_init.feature):**\n```\nAnd the directory \".ralph-burning/daemon/tasks\" should exist\nAnd the directory \".ralph-burning/daemon/leases\" should exist\n```\n\n**Reuse Potential:**\n- Agent execution infrastructure for daemon-driven stages (invocation contracts, capability checks, timeout/cancellation)\n- Requirements drafting patterns for interactive flows (pause points, state transitions, journal events)\n- FS store patterns for atomic state persistence\n- Stub backend for deterministic testing\n\n---\n\n### **Current Test Surface**\n- **Unit tests:** 303 tests (`tests/unit/`)\n- **CLI integration tests:** 75+ tests (`tests/cli.rs`)\n- **Conformance Gherkin:** 14 feature files with 60+ scenarios\n- **Total lines of test code:** ~13,000 lines\n\n**Relevant test files for daemon integration:**\n- `tests/conformance/features/workspace_init.feature` — daemon directory expectations\n- `tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature` — standard flow execution patterns (daemon will use same)\n- `tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature` — state machine patterns (requirements is like a daemon task)\n- `tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs` — journal event patterns (daemon will emit similar events)\n\n---\n\n### **Key Architecture Points for Loop 11 (Daemon Routing)**\n\n1. **Generalized Contract Interface** (Loop 10) — agent_execution no longer tied to workflow-only contracts, enabling daemon-driven invocations with their own contract types\n2. **Flow Semantics** (Loop 9) — all four flow presets (standard, docs_change, ci_improvement, quick_dev) now executable via unified engine\n3. **Amendment Queue Infrastructure** (Loop 8) — durable amendment persistence for late-stage acceptance workflows\n4. **Completion Rounds** (Loop 8) — multi-turn refinement model already in place\n5. **Journal Events** — all state transitions already persist journal events, providing daemon audit trail\n6. **State Recovery** — resume logic reconstructs state from journal, enabling daemon restart resilience\n\nThe daemon will likely:\n- Monitor `.ralph-burning/daemon/tasks/` for work items\n- Use lease files in `.ralph-burning/daemon/leases/` for concurrent-safety\n- Drive projects through flows using generalized `execute_run()` / `resume_run()` \n- Emit daemon-specific journal events alongside project run events\n- Handle interactive flows (quick_dev, requirements) via pause/resume mechanics already demonstrated in requirements_drafting"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9f2d296937b56f5d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56189\ntool_uses: 56\nduration_ms: 82564</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac8d6a2a-5f6d-4606-9741-7014e6740f51","uuid":"889647fb-84b4-42ed-a454-c809f025dfb3","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following files to understand the current project state and what loop 10 delivered:\n\n1. The loop 10 spec: loops/010-requirements-drafting-and-project-seed-handoff/20260312193814-spec.md\n2. The master prompt: prompt.md (if it exists at the root)\n3. Any existing daemon-related conformance features: look in tests/conformance/features/ for anything mentioning daemon, task, lease, routing, watcher, rebase, 